President Robert Mugabe was a very happy man on Thursday afternoon after seeing his long time friend, Jacob Zuma. He told President Jacob Zuma he s pleased to see his counterpart is still in one piece.Speaking at the opening of a Bi-National Commission in Harare on Thursday, the 92-year old leader told his South African counterpart: &#8220;Comrade president, we need each other even more now than before.&#8221;&#8220;We are happy you are still in one piece in spite of what the papers are writing every day.&#8221; He added.&#8220;Zuma and I are going to rule forever. Even if I die, I will be reborn in another body and rule Zimbabwe again &#8221; Said Mugabe.